Energy XXI (Bermuda) Ltd.  rose 1.5
percent after announcing an agreement yesterday to buy Gulf of
Mexico assets from Exxon Mobil Corp. for $1.01 billion.  Energy XXI will pay down debt quickly so itâ€™s ready for
more purchases,  John Schiller , chief executive officer of the
Hamilton, Bermuda-based oil-exploration company, said on a
conference call today. The company may retire $150 million in
 debt  next year, Chief Financial Officer  David West Griffin  said
on the call.  The  shares  rose 39 cents to $25.73 at 4:09 p.m. on the
